## ğŸ§  What is Static Routing?
Static routing is a method where routes are manually configured
by a network administrator. It is suitable for small and predictable networks.

## ğŸ—ºï¸ Network Topology
- Two routers connected using a point-to-point link
- Each router has one LAN
